quran[22]{c,v,t,f}:
  54,50,"Our command is but a single word<sup>20</sup>, which is fulfilled in the blink of an eye.","[20] Our command when We want something, We only say, ""Be,"" and it is."
  54,51,"We have destroyed many like you [O Makkans]<sup>21</sup>; is there anyone to take heed?","[21] In rejecting Allah's messengers."
  54,52,"Everything they did is in the written records,",""
  54,53,"and everything, small or big, is written down.",""
  54,54,"Indeed, the righteous will be in gardens and rivers<sup>22</sup>,","[22] Rivers of water, honey, milk, and wine. See 47:15."
  54,55,"seated in honor in the presence of the Most Powerful Sovereign.",""
  55,1,"The Most Compassionate,",""
  55,2,"has taught the Qurâ€™an,",""
  55,3,"He created man,",""
  55,4,"and taught him speech.",""
  55,5,"The sun and the moon follow their precise courses,",""
  55,6,"and the stars<sup>1</sup> and trees prostrate [to Allah]<sup>2</sup>.","[1] ""Najm"" is also a vegetation without a trunk, stalk, or stem.\n [2] i.e., they obediently submit to the laws of Allah. See 22:18."
  55,7,"He raised the heaven and enjoined justice",""
  55,8,"so that you may not transgress the limits of justice.",""
  55,9,"Therefore establish weights in justice, and do not give short measure.",""
  55,10,"He has spread out the earth for all creatures,",""
  55,11,"in which there are fruits and palm trees with date stalks,",""
  55,12,"and grain having chaff, and fragrant plants.",""
  55,13,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you<sup>3</sup> deny?","[3] i.e., men and jinn."
  55,14,"He created man from dry clay like pottery,",""
  55,15,"and He created the jinn from a smokeless flame of fire.",""
  55,16,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you deny?",""
